    "For SA, Q self t = X t W self Q and K self t = X t W self K. For CA, Q cross t = X t W cross Q and K cross t = T W cross K. For a head of width d h at layer l, the per-headattention maps are SA h l (X t) = softmax(Q self t K self t ⊤ / √ d h) ∈ [0, 1] HW ×HW, CA h l (X t,T) = softmax(Q cross t K cross t ⊤ / √ d h) ∈ [0, 1] HW ×L.We register hooks on all attention layers to read out SA and CA without altering computation."
